    "body": "> KMiri doesn't soundly handle `extern fn` or external symbol addresses:\n> \n> ```\n> __einit_array=0xffffffff80014fad __sinit_array=0xffffffff80014fcf\n> An uncaught panic occurred: panicked at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/lib.rs:189:20:\n> attempt to subtract with overflow\n> ```\n> \n> Symbols `__sinit_array` and `__einit_array` are generated by linker, so kmiri should ideally reject unknown  symbols.\n> \n> But currently kmiri allocates the symbols even if they don't exist. Miri doesn't have the problem, because such code won't link after  compilation. [playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2024&gist=3d8b281041152abaf613a9005dcbfe8a) \n\n _Originally posted by @zjp-CN in [#75](https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/75#issuecomment-4809825065)_",
